Interface Versionable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    _AdHocStringVersioned, _BaselineConfigurationVersion, _Genericizable, _MPMCompatible, _SerialNumberedInstanceVersion, _ViewManageable, AdHocStringVersioned, BaselineConfigurationVersion, Genericizable, MPMCompatible, SerialNumberedInstanceVersion, ViewManageable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    _AccessControlSurrogate, _DefaultWTContainerTemplate, _EnterpriseData, _EPMDocument, _MPMControlCharacteristic, _MPMMfgProcess, _MPMMfgStandardGroup, _MPMOperation, _MPMPlant, _MPMProcessPlan, _MPMResource, _MPMResourceGroup, _MPMSequence, _MPMStandardCC, _OptionSet, _PartList, _WTPart, _WTProductConfiguration, AccessControlSurrogate, DefaultWTContainerTemplate, EnterpriseData, EPMDocument, MPMControlCharacteristic, MPMMfgProcess, MPMMfgStandardGroup, MPMOperation, MPMPlant, MPMProcessPlan, MPMResource, MPMResourceGroup, MPMSequence, MPMStandardCC, OptionSet, PartList, WTPart, WTProductConfiguration

    @GenAsPersistable(interfaces=Iterated.class,
                  extendable=true)
public interface Versionable
    Plug-n-play interface indicating that the object is versioned in some manner, i.e. it has logical branches identified in some manner and thought of as versions. This tagging interface does not assert how these versions are identified, and is predominantly used on the server side to simplify and group code used to create versions. All branching (versioning) mechanisms should extend this interface.

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: true
